item.value: parameter controls the number of times the * pattern is applied and therefore affects the length of the resulting * array. If the limit n is greater than zero then the pattern * will be applied at most n - 1 times, the array's * length will be no greater than n, and the array's last entry * will contain all input beyond the last matched delimiter.
